author: Jason Lemon
title: South Korea Sees Rise In 'Reactivated' Coronavirus Patients Who Were Initially Cured of Virus
description: "A study into how immunity is developed after COVID-19 infection is still ongoing," Jeong Eun-Kyeong, the director of Korea's Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said.
content:
South Korea has seen a rise in the number of people who recovered from the coronavirus and have now again tested positive, drawing concern and confusion as the country looks toward easing social distancing guidelines.
